article.headline: USC 93, Arizona State 84
article.story: TEMPE, Ariz. (AP) -- Held in check for most of the second half Saturday night, Desmon Farmer knew his time would come. It finally did in overtime. Farmer scored 10 of his 25 points in the extra period, helping Southern California beat Arizona State 93-84 to move into a tie for seventh place with Washington State in the Pac-10 Conference. Errick Craven added a season-high 26 points for the Trojans (10-12, 5-8 Pac-10), who atoned for a 41.9 percent effort from the field by making 32 of 40 attempts from the free-throw line. The last-place Sun Devils (9-13, 3-10) got 19 points and nine rebounds from Ike Diogu, whose night was cut short when he fouled out with 3:44 left in overtime. It marked only the fifth time in 54 games that Diogu had fouled out. "We basically cut off the head of the monster," USC coach Henry Bibby said of Diogu. "We held Ike to 19 points, and we got him to foul out just going at him and getting him to pick up fouls." The Trojans took control in overtime on quick baskets by McMillan and Farmer, and went 12 for 14 from the line in the closing two minutes to seal the deal. Their 32 free throws were the most in 22 games this season. "I knew I had to not try to do too much, and not try to be fancy," said Farmer, whose 25 points were the most he had scored since Feb. 5, when he posted 31 against Washington. "I just kept it basic."
